  "suggestion": "Efficiency failure is mostly movement cost + threshold misalignment. Move less, harvest more selectively, conserve harder.; Efficiency (0.156) is critically low — entities are burning energy faster than harvesting. The culprits: (1) high moveSpeed on explorers wastes energy per tick, (2) very low harvestThreshold on aggressive harvesters (0.05-0.08) causes energy-negative harvests on marginal resources, (3) global energyConserve too low. Secondary issue: rhythm (0.234) is weak — low pulseFrequency values don't create temporal patterns. Fix: reduce moveSpeed across the board, raise harvestThreshold to selective range (0.10-0.15), boost energyConserve, and increase pulseFrequency for rhythm.",
